               <head>Mukhtasar of Majlisi, juz' 2</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Majlisī, Muḥammad Taqī ibn Maqṣūd ʻAlī, 1594 or 5-1659 or 60</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007003439 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008121357 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111617" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_64B-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_118731817">Majlisī, Muḥammad Taqī ibn Maqṣūd ʻAlī, 1594 or 5-1659 or 60</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_118731817">مجلسي، محمد تقي بن مقصود علي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Abridged translation, here entitled <title>Mukhtaṣar</title>, by Muḥammad Taqī Majlisī based on a larger Arabic treatise on Shīʿī doctrine by the early scholar <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_90043815" ref="https://lccn.loc.gov/nr90021741" role="ant">Abū Jaʿfar Muḥammad ibn ʿAlī ibn Ḥusayn ibn Mūsá ibn Bābūyah (Bābavayh) Qummī</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>The present volume consists of juzʾ 2
</p>
                        <p>Multiple dated colophons (ff. 174r, 377r, 457r): 1) 1 Shavvāl 1215/15 February 1801 by <persName key="person_f7122" role="scr">Fayz̤ Allāh</persName>; 2) Rabīʿ al-S̲ānī 1107 (sic, read 1207)/16 November 1792 by <persName key="person_f7122" role="scr">Fayz̤ Allāh</persName>; 3) 1 Muḥarram 1200/4 November 1785

                        </p>
                        <p>Some replacement folios added later in shikastah, otherwise the volume is in a simple rounded naskh hand
</p>
                        <p>Gilt and polychrome rulings; crude illuminated headpieces added later 
</p>
                        <p>Creased, crumpled, and torn; severely damaged by fungal and water stains; unbound; very fragile </p>
                     </note>
